pr_title: feat: added prettier and editor config
pr_body:
@romain-fontugne sir, I have added:
- A prettier configuration file specifying the basic needs
- A prettier ignore file which confirms which all files prettier should not run
- An Editor configuration file, generally by default developers have their own editor configs globally defined which may create a conflict due to prettier and their own file definition. I have defined a set of editor configs that will run and keep the code in sync all together. 

In `.eslintrc.js` although `extends: ["plugin:vue/essential", "@vue/prettier"],` is defined but prettier was not running I suppose the issue was not defining the `.prettierrc` file. I hope this PR closes #30. Incase you want me to change some of the defined configs let me know would be more than happy to work and resolve them. 

Cheers!
Aniket

pr_body:
I have added:
- Pull Request template
- Bug Report template
- Feature Request template
- Dependabot bot automation script

As of now, the bot runs weekly. I believe keeping the checks for a daily update will make it a bit difficult to check the breakpoints and doing it bi-weekly would be too late for attackers to attack or package depreciation. 

Let me know what you think about it? If you want me to change anything let me know I will do it asap. Till then I am working on another issue assigned to me and creating some more :)

Closes #26
